The MLD of the mice and LD50 of E. coli were 2.925×107 and 0.911×106 CFU/kg, respectively (Table S4). After 5 days of prophylactic administration of geraniol, significant antibacterial activity was observed in the mice challenged with MLD of E. coli. Geraniol at 0.261 g/kg completely (100%) prevented E. coli infection. The prevention rate decreased with the decrease in dose, and the drug dose of 0.0944 g/kg was considered as the ED50 of geraniol against E. coli infected mice (Table S5). Similar to cefotaxime, geraniol cured 100% of infection in the mice challenged with LD50 of E. coli (Table S6). The routine blood indices, including WBC, LYM, MID, GRA, PCT, PLT, RBC, MPV, and MCV, significantly decreased after infection (p < 0.05; 
Figure S2
